vels, the person closest to the mob will be the one the mob attacks.  When we say to nuke from melee range, it's to keep the mob from running after you IF you get agro and making the melees run after it.<br>
<br>
The high end game gets a little strange when it comes to things like this because if you have a good level of hit points(1700+ unbuffed), with epic rune or force shield, in a group if a mob that hits for over 300 hits you, that's not a big deal.  There are times when a mob with low HP that has agroed will just inspire me to use draughts to nuke it down rather than be concerned.  It's also not unusual to find yourself with over 4k HP in the high level game when fully buffed.  Then you REALLY need to be careful of agro, but it's still generally not a big deal when a mob that hits for 600+ slaps you a few times before switching back to the tanks.  Concussion definately helps.  <br>
<br>
One thing to keep in mind, the sooner you agro, the harder it is for a melee to pull the mob off you.  Depending on the damage output from the others in your group, you can either start to cast big nukes at 80% mob health, or you may need to wait until it's down to 60%.  It's really about judging agro.  Another thing that many don't realize is that a paladin or shadow knight will often get and hold agro a LOT easier than a warrior.  This is why Verant/Sony MUST work on warrior agro.  Taunt for warriors should do a LOT more than it does currently. <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 65 Wizard<br>
